<p class=3D"MsoNormal">Hi Fellow SHARPies.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">I=E2=80=99d been thinking about this for some time no=
w, but wanted to express my gratitude to this crew for the excellent and tho=
ught provoking conversations over the years. One of the topics that I had wo=
rked on and dug deep into at the 2010 SHARP,
 looking at music in terrorism and also thinking about how we might apply mo=
dels of behavior change to terrorist propaganda ended up having a significan=
t influence on my research in the years that followed.
<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">In 2015, after a few years of developing ideas and pr=
oposals, and figuring out the right composition of an interdisciplinary team=
; we ended up getting $2.3M in support from DOD as part of the Minerva Initi=
ative for the =E2=80=9CMobilizing Media=E2=80=9D
 project. The team has generated over a hundred presentations, several books=
, and I think we are closing in on something like 50 articles and chapters t=
hat have been published as part of this effort. Several Masters and Disserta=
tion projects came from all of
 this too.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">One example from this effort that I think would be of=
 interest: We also came up with an application, which started as a way to ke=
ep track of what pieces of music (anashid in this case) were embedded in whi=
ch videos, and how they were being
 used. Starting off as a data management challenge, we realized that our tec=
hnology and subject matter expertise (a catalog of over 1200 jihadi themed a=
nashid, produced by ISIS and others, for instance) that could slice videos i=
nto 10 second increments and
 by querying against a cloud based database (our =E2=80=98bucket=E2=80=99 of=
 songs) could pretty accurately tell us what audio was included in videos.&n=
bsp; At a meeting where we were talking Terrorism and Social Media, and with=
 colleagues from Facebook, and the Home Office in
 the UK (among others) we realized that the proof of concept in this had som=
e important implications for trying to identify terrorist-produced content o=
nline. (Paper that we published on this is attached in case anyone cares to c=
heck it out).<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">Others on the team did deep image and multimodal anal=
yses, and other members took computational linguistic approaches to look at l=
anguage use (for example, how metaphors are used, and the implications).<o:p=
></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">All this to say, that so much of where I traveled res=
earch-wise over the past decade really can trace back to those 5 weeks in Ar=
izona.
<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">So, thank you.&nbsp; And thank you for keeping the co=
nversation going.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">Hope you are all well,<o:p></o:p></p>
